\pagebreakNum

#### Archetypes

##### Cunning
___
- **Ability Scores:** Strength 6, Dexterity 14, Constitution 8, Intelligence 3, Wisdom 12, Charisma 6
- **Ability Score Points:** 2
- **Hit Die:** d8
- **Armor Class:** 11 + Dexterity modifier
- **Saving Throws:** Dexterity, Charisma
- **Speed:** 35 ft.
- ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* Dexterity modifier + proficiency bonus to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* d4 + Dexterity modifier piercing damage.
- ***Sneak Attack.*** Once per turn, your animal companion can deal an extra 1d6 damage to one creature it hit with an attack if it has advantage on the attack roll or at least one of the creature's allies are within 5 feet of it.

##### Ferocity
___
- **Ability Scores:** Strength 12, Dexterity 14, Constitution 8, Intelligence 3, Wisdom 10, Charisma 6
- **Ability Score Points:** 2
- **Hit Die:** d8
- **Armor Class:** 11 + Dexterity modifier
- **Saving Throws:** Strength, Dexterity
- **Speed:** 30 ft.
- ***Swipe.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* Dexterity modifier + proficiency bonus to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* d8 + Dexterity modifier bludgeoning damage.

##### Tenacity
___
- **Ability Scores:** Strength 12, Dexterity 10, Constitution 14, Intelligence 3, Wisdom 6, Charisma 8
- **Ability Score Points:** 2
- **Hit Die:** d10
- **Armor Class:** 12 + Constitution modifier
- **Saving Throws:** Constitution, Charisma
- **Speed:** 25 ft.
- ***Slam.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* Strength modifier + proficiency bonus to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* d6 + Strength modifier bludgeoning damage.
- ***Protective.*** When a creature your animal companion can see attacks a target that is within 5 feet of it, it can use its reaction to impose disadvantage on the attack roll.

\columnbreak

> #### Animal Companion Point Buy
> 
> The basic rules of the point buy method are:
> 
> - Each ability score begins at 8
> - Ability scores above 8 cost a certain number of points
> - Ability scores below 8 give you a certain number of points
> - You have 3 points to spend to increase scores
> - Maximum ability score is 17
> - Minimum ability score is 2
> - The ability score point cost table shows what you can spend your points on.
> 
> 
> 
> |Ability Score | Point Cost | Ability Score | Point Cost |
> |:---:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> | 2   | -19   | 10    | 2     | 
> | 3   | -14   | 11	| 3     |
> | 4   | -10   | 12	| 4     |
> | 5   | -7    | 13	| 5     |
> | 6   | -4    | 14	| 7     |
> | 7   | -2    | 15	| 9     |
> | 8   | 0     | 16    | 12    |
> | 9	| 1     | 17    | 16
>

> Alternative Point Buy Table (117 point budget)
> |Ability Score | Point Cost | Ability Score | Point Cost |
> |:---:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> | 2   | 0     | 10    | 21    | 
> | 3   | 5     | 11	| 22    |
> | 4   | 9     | 12	| 23    |
> | 5   | 12    | 13	| 24    |
> | 6   | 15    | 14	| 26    |
> | 7   | 17    | 15	| 28    |
> | 8   | 19    | 16    | 31    |
> | 9	| 20    | 17    | 35    |


\pagebreakNum

#### Companion Origin
##### Aberration
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Strength and Constitution scores increase by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Resistance (Psychic) wild feature.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving aberrations is increased by 2.

##### Beast
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** One of your animal companion's ability scores of your choice increases by 2, and another increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with any two Low tier wild features.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving beasts is decreased by 2.

##### Celestial
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Charisma scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Resistance (Radiant) and either the Locomotion (Flight) or Trained wild features.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving celestials is decreased by 1.

##### Construct [TBD]
Not included.
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Constitution scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Overtune and XXX wild features.
- ***Constructed Nature.*** Your animal companion doesn't require air, food, drink, or sleep.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving dragons is increased by 1.

##### Dragon
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Constitution scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Breath and Natural Defenses wild features.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving dragons is increased by 1.

##### Elemental
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Dexterity scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Immunity (any one) wild feature.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving elementals is increased by 1.

\columnbreak

##### Fey
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Charisma scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Cunning and Sleepless wild features.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving fey is increased by 1.

##### Fiend
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Intelligence scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Resistance (Fire) and Innate Spellcasting wild features.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving fiends is increased by 1.

##### Giant
Not included.

##### Humanoid
Not included.

##### Monstrosity
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Strength or Constitution score increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Keen Senses and one additional Low tier wild feature.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving monstrosities is increased by 1.

##### Ooze
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Dexterity scores increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Amorphous and Elemental Resistance (Poison) wild feature.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving oozes is increased by 2.

##### Plant
___
- ***Ability Score Increase.*** Your animal companion's Strength or Charisma score increases by 1.
- ***Bonus Wild Feature.*** Your animal companion starts with the Elemental Resistance (Poison) and False Appearance wild features.
- ***Fire Vulnerability.*** Your animal companion is vulnerable to fire damage.
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving dragons is decreased by 1.

##### Undead
Not included.
___
- ***Training Modifier.*** The DC of any training checks involving aberrations is increased by 2.
- ***Undead Nature.*** Your animal companion doesn't require air, food, drink, or sleep.


\pagebreakNum

### Wild Features
#### Low-Tier
##### Ability Score Increase
You can increase one of your animal companion's ability scores of your choice by 2, or you can increase two of its ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can’t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature. You can select this wild feature multiple times.

##### Aggressive
As a bonus action, your animal companion can move up to its speed towards a hostile creature that it can see.

##### Amphibious
Your animal companion can breathe air and water. If the animal companion does not already have a swim speed, it gains one equal to its movement speed with a value to its base speed -10 feet.

##### Cunning
Your animal companion has advantage on saving throws against being charmed.

##### Darkvision
Your animal companion has darkvision out to a range of 60 feet.

##### Dive Attack
If the animal companion is flying and dives at least 20 feet straight towards a target and then hits it with a melee attack, the attack deals an extra 4 (1d8) damage to the target.

##### Echolocation
Your animal companion has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing and blindsight with a range of 60 feet. It can't use its blindsight while deafened.

##### Hold Breath
Your animal companion can hold its breath for 15 minutes.

##### Keen Senses
Choose two from the following senses: hearing, sight, and smell. Your animal companion has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on those two senses.

##### Locomotion
Your animal companion can move in a unique way. Choose from burrow, climb, fly, or swim. Your animal companion gains that type of movement speed with a value equal to its base speed -10 feet.

##### Mimicry
Your animal companion can mimic any sounds it has heard, including voices. A creature that hears the sounds can tell they are imitations with a successful Wisdom (Insight) check with a DC equal to your companion's Feature save DC.

##### Mount
Your animal companion is large enough to be ridden by you. Unlike most mountable creatures, your animal companion can be your size or larger. The companion cannot be smaller than your character's size to take this wild feature. [Cannot fly unless it is larger than you.]

##### Natural Attack
Your animal companion gains a new form of natural attack (eg bite, claw, gore, trample, etc). This new attack deals 1d6 damage and you choose the type of damage the attack does and which ability score (except Constitution) the attack uses for its attack and damage bonuses. Melee attacks have a reach of 5 feet and ranged attacks have a range of 25/50 feet.

##### Natural Camouflage
Your animal companion has advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in one favored terrain of your choice from the ranger's Natural Explorer class feature.

##### Natural Defenses
Your animal companion increases its Armor Class by 1.

##### Nimble
Your animal companion is particularly quick. Its base land speed increases by 5 feet.

##### Poisonous
Your animal companion's basic attack deals an additional 2 (1d4) poison damage.

##### Powerful Attack
Your animal companion's basic attack increases its damage die by one size.

##### Protective Shell
Your animal companion's AC increases to 17; it does not gain a bonus to AC from having a positive Dexterity or Constitution modifier. It also gains the following action:

Stable. Whenever an effect knocks the turtle prone, it can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw to avoid being knocked prone. A prone turtle is upside down. To stand up, it must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity check on its turn and then use all its movement for that turn.

***Shell Defense.*** You can withdraw into your shell as an action. Until you emerge, you gain a +4 bonus to your AC, and you have advantage on Strength and Constitution saving throws. While in your shell, you are prone, your speed is 0 and can't increase, you have disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws, you can't take reactions, and the only action you can take is a bonus action to emerge from your shell.

\pagebreakNum

##### Reach
Your animal companion increases the range of one of its melee attacks by 5 feet. You can select this wild feature multiple times. Each time it is taken, choose a different melee attack.

##### Reckless
At the start of its turn, your animal companion can gain advantage on all melee attack rolls it makes during that turn, but attack rolls against it have advantage until the start of its next turn.

##### Skulk
Your animal companion can take its Hide action as a bonus action on each of its turns.

##### Slippery
Your animal companion is slick to the touch. It has advantage on ability checks and saving throws made to escape a grapple or being restrained.

##### Stable
Your animal companion is particularly sure-footed. ???????????????

##### Standing Leap
Your animal companion's long jump is up to 20 feet and its high jump is up to 10 feet, with or without a running start.

##### Stench
The animal companion produces some form of noxious gas or stench around it. Any creature that starts its turn within 5 feet of your animal companion must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be poisoned until the start of its next turn. On a successful saving throw, the creature is immune to its Stench for 24 hours.

##### Sticky
Your animal companion is sticky to the touch. Attempts it makes to make or maintain a grapple have advantage.

##### Trained
Your animal companion gains proficiency in two skills of your choice. You can take this wild feature multiple times. Each time it is taken, select two different skills your animal companion gains proficiency with.

##### Trip
When your animal companion hits a creature with its basic attack, the target must make a DC XX Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.

##### Web Weaver
Your animal companion ignores movement restrictions caused by webbing. While in contact with a web, the spider knows the exact location of any other creature in contact with the same web. It also gains the following action:

***Web (Recharge 5-6).*** *Ranged Weapon Attack:* Dexterity modifier + proficiency bonus to hit, range 30/60 ft., one Large or smaller creature. *Hit:* The creature is restrained by webbing. As an action, the restrained creature can make a Strength check against your Feature save DC, escaping the webbing on a success. The effect ends if the webbing is destroyed. The webbing has AC 10, 5 hit points, resistance to bludgeoning damage, and immunity to poison and psychic damage.

\pagebreakNum

#### Medium-Tier
##### Ambusher
Your animal companion has advantage on attack rolls against any creature it has surprised.

##### Armored
Your animal companion increases its Armor Class by 1.

##### Avoidance
Choose one ability score. If your animal companion is subjected to a spell or effect that allows it to make a saving throw with that ability score to only take half damage, it instead takes no damage if it succeeds on the saving throw, and only half damage if it fails.

##### Charger
Your animal companion gains the Charger feat.

##### Constrict
Your animal companion can crush creatures it grapples. As a bonus action, when the companion has a creature grappled it cna deal 1d8 + Strength modifier damage to the grappled creature.

##### Hemorrhaging
Your animal companion's attacks cause deep internal or external bleeding on creatures struck by its basic attack. When a struck creature starts their turn, the target loses 4 (1d8) hit point due to blood loss. At the end of each of the creature's turn it can attempt a Constitution saving throw with a DC equal to 8 + your animal companion's Strength modifier + its proficiency bonus to end this effect. Magical healing or regeneration also end this effect.

##### Improved Difficulty
Your animal companion is more skilled in the use of its abilities. It increases the DC of its wild features by 1.

##### Pack Tactics
Your animal companion has advantage on attack rolls against a creature if at least one of its allies are within 5 feet of the target and the ally isn't incapacitated.

##### Pounce
If the animal companion moves at least 20 feet straight towards a target and then hits it with a melee attack on the same turn, the creature must make a DC XX Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. If the target is prone, the animal companion can then make one melee attack against it as a bonus action.

##### Rampage
When your animal companion reduces a creature to 0 hit points with a melee attack on its turn, it can take a bonus action to move up to half its speed and make a basic attack against another target.

##### Spider Climb
The animal companion can climb difficult surfaces, including upside down on ceilings, without needing to make an ability check. It must have a climb speed to take this wild feature.

##### Swift
Your animal companion is especially quick. Its base land speed increases by 10 feet. This stacks with the Nimble trait.

##### Venomous
Your animal companion's basic attack is venomous. Creatures hit by its attack must make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the target is poisoned until the end of its next turn.

##### Wounded Fury
While you or your animal companion have 10 hit points or fewer, your animal companion has advantage on attack rolls. In addition, it deals an extra 7 (2d6) damage to any target it hits with a melee attack.

#### High Tier
##### Blood Frenzy
Your animal companion deals 3 (1d6) extra damage and has advantage that doesn't have all of its hit points.

##### Masterful Difficulty
Your animal companion is a master at using its abilities. It increases the DC of its wild features by 1. This wild feature stacks with the Improved Difficulty wild feature.

##### Speedy
Your animal companion is exceptionally quick. Its base land speed increases by 15 feet. This stacks with the Nimble and Swift traits.

\pagebreakNum

#### Unknown Tier
##### Alternative Primary Movement
Able to switch your primary movement from walking to burrow, climb, fly, or swim. Makes your walking speed a lot lower, but gives a faster other movement speed.
##### Aquatic
##### Charge
##### Defensive Quills
##### Desert Dweller

##### Howl
##### [Infectious Bite]
Rats, hyenas.
##### Moth Dust attack
##### Phosphorescence
Fireflies, deep sea fish
##### Pin
You can grapple a target with an attack.
##### Pounce
##### Powerful Build
##### Prowl
Sneak Attack?
##### Relentless
##### Rend/Ravage
Reduce armor
##### Screech
##### Shell Spin
Turtle based ability, able to spin in place and attack nearby creatures.
##### Snatch
Can attempt a disarm

